<p>Hostel life reviews split by room type. Single-occupancy hostel residents (typically PGPM students) consistently rate hostel quality 4.5–5/5. Double-occupancy Year 1 PGDM students rate it 3.8–4.2/5 — the rooms are functional and air-conditioned but compact when shared. The hostel culture in Year 1 PGDM is described as social and collaborative (study groups form naturally in shared rooms), which some students value and others find difficult for deep individual study.</p>

